In 2014 the Ministry of Health began implementation of the National program for prevention of chronic non-communicable diseases 2014-2020 program. In the program are planning following surveys:
- prevalence of tobacco consumption among different population groups; 
- determining the frequency and dynamics of morbidity and mortality by reason of tobacco use;
-economic consequences of tobacco use; 
-costs of the health care system in the treatment of diseases associated with the use of tobacco products;
- level of passive smoking. 
-establishment the effectiveness of educational programs for health risks of smoking and exposure to tobacco smoke.

